	<Title>
		Focus on fit when shoe shopping
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;To find shoes that fit properly, try these tips: 1. Have your feet measured. Shoe size can change as you age. 2. Ask the salesperson to measure both feet. If one foot is larger than the other, try on a pair that fits your larger foot. 3. Shop for shoes in the early afternoon after you&apos;ve been walking for some time, when your feet are at their largest.&lt;/p&gt;
